#compdef obs-scene-switcher
# =============================================================================
# obs-scene-switcher — Christian Muehlhaeuser (muesli)'s
#                      "Tracks your active window and
#                      switches OBS scenes accordingly" — a
#                      Go CLI for OBS Studio livestreamers
#                      that auto-switches scenes based on
#                      which application window has focus.
#                      Connects to OBS via WebSocket
#                      (obs-websocket protocol) and uses
#                      X11 active-window detection (Linux)
#                      to determine focus.  Configurable via
#                      a TOML file mapping window class +
#                      window name patterns to scene names.
#                      Distinguishing from obs-cli, OBS's
#                      built-in scripting, AHK-based scene
#                      switchers, and other automation tools
#                      by:
#                        - WINDOW-DRIVEN SCENE SELECTION —
#                          tracks active X11 window via
#                          BurntSushi/xgb + xgbutil; when
#                          window changes, looks up matching
#                          scene rule + switches OBS scene
#                          via WebSocket
#                        - SCENES.TOML CONFIG FILE — TOML
#                          mapping of patterns to scene names:
#                            [[scenes]]
#                            scene_name = "Browser Scene"
#                            window_class = "Firefox"
#
#                            [[scenes]]
#                            scene_name = "Coding Scene"
#                            window_class = "kitty"
#                            window_name = "vim"
#
#                            [[away_scenes]]
#                            scene_name = "BRB"
#                            window_class = "Slack"
#                          Each rule's window_class /
#                          window_name fields are matched
#                          against the active window's
#                          XGetClassHint / XGetWMName results
#                        - AWAY-SCENES SECTION — distinct
#                          [[away_scenes]] block for when the
#                          streamer focuses non-streaming
#                          apps (Slack, email, etc.) — auto-
#                          BRB transition
#                        - obs-websocket PROTOCOL via go-obs-
#                          websocket — connects to OBS at
#                          host:port (default localhost:4444),
#                          subscribes to events, issues
#                          SetCurrentScene requests
#                        - X11 ACTIVE WINDOW DETECTION via
#                          BurntSushi/xgb + xgbutil — pure-
#                          Go X11 client; reads _NET_ACTIVE_
#                          WINDOW root property + XEvent
#                          PropertyNotify to react to focus
#                          changes
#                        - RECENT WINDOW STACK (15-deep) —
#                          tracks recent windows; for "go
#                          back to previous" scene transitions
#                        - LINUX-ONLY (X11) — Wayland not
#                          supported; macOS / Windows not
#                          supported (would require different
#                          window-tracking APIs)
#                        - CHARMBRACELET ECOSYSTEM ADJACENT —
#                          author muesli also maintains gum,
#                          glow, mango, kmeans-color-engine,
#                          and is a co-founder + maintainer of
#                          the Charm CLI ecosystem (charmbracelet
#                          org); broader contribution to Go
#                          CLI design
#                      Used by: Linux livestreamers using OBS
#                      Studio who want scene automation
#                      without manual hotkey switching,
#                      streamers managing complex multi-app
#                      workflows (gaming + browser + chat +
#                      face cam), and as a reference
#                      implementation of BurntSushi/toml +
#                      BurntSushi/xgb + spf13/cobra +
#                      go-obs-websocket composition in Go.
#
# Author:  Christian Muehlhaeuser (muesli@gmail.com, muesli
#          on GitHub) — German Go developer, co-founder of
